    </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font face="Haettenschweiler, Tahoma, Arial, sans-serif" size="5" COLOR="#000000">Strategy</Font></TD><TD><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size="2">NOTE: Everything in caps is important. Don&#39;t just judge the deck by th cards. <br />
<br />
BIDDING - It does not really matter what you bid. Just don&#39;t be stupid. <br />
<br />
THE FREE PEOPLE - There are a lot of mounts, because you never know who is going to play Dunland (I will spell that out for you - discard possesions). Everyone needs to be mounted. The bows go to the Swordsmen, as do the Elven Swords.<br />
Arwen is a good support card.  She can beat the crap out almost every minion.<br />
You don&#39;t have to play Shadowfax on Gandalf, thats too conditional...you can use a Horse of Rohan on him or Brego...doesn&#39;t really matter...<br />
Aside from that - the FREE PEOPLE ARE MADE TO RUN - NOT PLAY SILLY GAMES WITH MINIONS. They are quick and strong - I side barred all other stategies at this time. <br />
<br />
MINIONS - Uruks are TRACKERS AND FOR THE MOST PART FIERCE. That is why I have the conditions I do. They are supposed to tick off the Opponent - prevent discarding Hobbits and stuff like that. Put WEARY on the opponents BIG COMPANIONS. DO NOT WASTE WEARY. Then use the other conditions to discard the Opp&#39;s conditions and take control of sites. <br />
<br />
Almost the same strategy, lacking Eomer and Theoden - and I changed up some minions...<br />
